        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 12:19PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 1219 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Dannelly Reservoir, or 11 miles northeast of Camden, moving southeast
at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dannelly Reservoir, Carlowville, Minter, and Tilden.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
